answer to question two:

The industrial revolution comes to mind, because of the high demand of machineary that paved the way of enginerring new 
technology that gave many people jobs and allowed companies to expand all over the country. The working conditions in these 
facilities are the draw back of the industrial revoultion where the poeple that consumed the products were happy but the 
people making these components suffered.
